wikipedia_page.main: Gabrielle Margaret Lambrick MA, FRHist Soc (23 August 1913 – 14 August 1968) was a British senior civil servant, educator and historian. After a distinguished career in the civil service during World War II she married and became a historian on medieval Abingdon in Oxfordshire and its environs. She was elected a Fellow of the Royal Historical Society in 1967.
